sentences: Diogenes Rivas (born October 4, 1942) is a dedicated Venezuelan composer as well as a researcher of contemporary music.
Later on, in Caracas, his teachers were Moleiro Moses and Inocente Carreño (from 1954 to 1957).
He continued his studies at the Academia Santa Cecilia in Rome, Italy, from 1958 to 1964.
He also studied conducting with Sir John Barbirolli and Carlo Zecchi in Taormina, Italy and with Bruno Maderna in Salzburg, Austria (1968).
He studied composition with Alfred Nieman in London from 1975 to 1977.
Since 1980 he is dedicated exclusively to composing.
In 2013, Rivas received  the Ordre des Arts et des Lettres (Order of the Arts and Letters) by the French government.
Since 1993, this Festival is dedicated to the international diffusion of outstanding contemporary repertory as well as that of traditional music from all periods of history.
The Atempo Festival celebrated its 17th anniversary in July 2010 with an audience of more than 4,000 attending the three-day event.

Throughout its uninterrupted history of nearly two decades, the Festival has presented 666 musical works of 320 different composers; 102 world premieres of works written especially for the Festival; 262 premieres for Venezuela, and 42 commissions, including 2 collective works in 191 concerts.
